abstract: Arthur Keenan, a child 3  years old, was found sick with smallpox in the apartments of its parents, in the tenement house No. 2,203 Fourth-avenue. abstract: HAMILTON, Ontario, July 10.--A boiler explosion occurred in the West Flamborough Paper Mills, eight miles northwest of this city, last evening, with fatal results. Edward Maloney, fireman, was blown about 25 feet and instantly killed. John A. Stutt, a member of the firm, was struck on the head and killed. Samuel Adams, who was working in an outbuilding some distance away, was badly hurt by the collapse of the roof over him.

abstract: CHICAGO, July 10.--Jesse W. Cook, the restaurant keeper who disappeared suddenly last Saturday night, returned home to-day.
